					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of land for offerings, with 4 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of rice daily during the <hi rend="italic">ardhayāma</hi> service in the temple of Mahādēva, and for burning a perpetual lamp before the god, by <hi rend="bold">Ādittaṉ Vīmaṉ</hi> of Kumārapāḍi (mentioned above in No. 30) <hi rend="bold">the chief of Aṇḍuṟai.</hi> The donor is surmised to have been the <hi rend="bold">father of Vīmaṉ Kundavaiyār the queen of Ariñjaya</hi> (<hi rend="italic">M.E.R.</hi> for 1928, Part II. para 3).</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
